President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has proclaimed September 18-24, 2022, as National Farm Safety and Health Week. This is a commitment to improving the safety and well-being of farmers, farmworkers, and ranchers who play a vital role in feeding the nation and sustaining communities. The article highlights the challenges faced by farmers, such as extreme weather, fluctuating commodity prices, accidents, and injuries. The administration is taking steps to support the implementation of health and safety standards on farms and ranches, including financial assistance and training programs. They are also making health insurance more affordable and accessible and investing in mental health resources for agricultural workers. The government has provided financial assistance for agricultural producers impacted by natural disasters and grants for farmworkers affected by the COVID-19 pandemic. The proclamation calls for the protection of the health and safety of farmers, farmworkers, and ranchers and expresses gratitude for their service to the nation.